    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section mb-5">
        <div class="container">
            <h3 class="text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
            <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed faq-question" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq1">
            Q. How do I install the LockNDock™ Cleat?
          </button>
        </h2>
                    <div id="faq1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                        <div class="accordion-body faq-answer">
             A: Installation is quick and easy. Simply insert the cleat between dock boards, rotate it 90° to lock beneath the dock, and pull it towards the dock edge to secure it in place. No tools, drilling, or bolts are required.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed faq-question" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq2">
            Q: Will the LockNDock™ Cleat damage my dock?
          </button>
        </h2>
                    <div id="faq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                        <div class="accordion-body faq-answer">
                            A: No, the cleat is designed to lock securely beneath the dock boards without causing any damage. It provides a reliable tie-off point without drilling or leaving permanent hardware.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed faq-question" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq4">
            Q: Is the LockNDock™ Cleat durable in saltwater environments?
          </button>
        </h2>
                    <div id="faq4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                        <div class="accordion-body faq-answer">
                            A: Yes, the cleat is made from high-grade 316 stainless steel, which is corrosion-resistant and built to withstand the harshest saltwater conditions.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed faq-question" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq3">
            Q: How easy is it to remove the LockNDock™ Cleat?
          </button>
        </h2>
                    <div id="faq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                        <div class="accordion-body faq-answer">
                            A: Removing the cleat is just as easy as installing it. Simply rotate the cleat back and lift it out from beneath the dock boards.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header">
          <button class="accordion-button collapsed faq-question" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq5">
            Q: What size watercraft is the LockNDock™ Cleat suitable for?
          </button>
        </h2>
                    <div id="faq5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                        <div class="accordion-body faq-answer">
                            A: The LockNDock™ Cleat is ideal for PWCs and small watercraft, providing a reliable tie-off point wherever you dock.
                        </div>
                    </div> 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

